<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">

 <head>
 
  <title>CSS Test: Direction applied to element with 'display' set to inline-block</title>

  <link rel="author" title="GÃ©rard Talbot" href="http://www.gtalbot.org/BrowserBugsSection/css21testsuite/" />
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visuren.html#direction" />
  <link rel="match" href="direction-applies-to-007-ref.xht" />

  <meta name="flags" content="ahem" />
  <meta name="assert" content="The 'direction' property applies to elements with a display of inline-block. Since 'direction' property is inherited, then it will be propagated into its subtree and then it can have a rendering effect on its block container descendants." />

  <style type="text/css">
  span#inline-block
  {
  background: orange;
  direction: rtl;
  display: inline-block;
  font: 50px/1em Ahem;
  width: 100px;
  }

  span.block-descendant
  {
  display: block;
  height: 50px;
  }
  </style>
 
 </head>
 
 <body>
 
  <p>Test passes if there is a black square in the <strong>upper-right corner</strong> of the orange square.</p>

  <div>
      <span id="inline-block">
			    <span class="block-descendant">a</span>        
				  <span class="block-descendant"></span>
      </span>
  </div>

 </body>
</html>